title: Mariners improve to 8-0
text:
HTR Media 6:39 p.m. CDT October 12, 2015 Football in motion over grass (Photo: Getty Images) 40 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Marcus Alfaro Jr. threw for 308 yards and three touchdowns as the Manitowoc County Mariners collected a win over the Wausau Jaguars on Saturday to improve to 8-0 on the season. 
Alfaro finished 13-of-20 in the air and also ran for 34 yards and a touchdown in the game. 
Steve Strong caught three passes – including two for touchdowns – for 138 yards. One of the touchdowns came on an 85-yard pass from Alfaro. 
John Wagner led the defense with five tackles and two pass break-ups, while Jacob Walesh had a pair of interceptions. Read or Share this story: http://htrne.ws/1RDodWp TOP VIDEOS
